articles.content:
A proprietor of a registered trademark who requests Customs to detain articles that are suspected of infringing the rights in the trademark shall make such request in writing to customs office of importation/exportation of such articles, accompanied by the following:
1. facts of the infringement, along with the descriptions which may sufficiently identify the infringing articles and the electronic files that contain the information for confirming the infringing articles, such as samples, photos, catalogs or pictures of genuine articles and counterfeit articles;
2. relevant substantive information, including name of importer/exporter, articles, ports and dates of importation/exportation, ship or flight numbers, container numbers, storage location, etc.;
3. proof of trademark registration.
Where the request is made by an agent, proof of appointment shall be submitted additionally.

A request for detention of articles that are suspected of infringing the rights in the trademark shall be accompanied by a security in an amount equivalent to the duty-paid price of the imported articles or the F.O.B. price of the exported articles, assessed by Customs, or the following equivalent assurance:
1. bonds published by the government;
2. certificate of bank deposit;
3. certificate of credit cooperative deposit;
4. trust certificate from investment company over one year; or
5. guarantee from loan institution.
A pledge for subparagraphs (1) through (4) of the preceding paragraph shall be established with Customs.

Customs may follow the procedures in accordance with applicable Customs Regulations on import and export articles clearance after retaining a representative sample if any of the following exists and such articles do not violate any regulations of clearance:
1. Customs revokes the detention pursuant to the preceding article;
2.the owner of detained articles requests Customs to revoke the detention pursuant to Article 6 of these Regulations;
3.the proprietor of the registered trademark requests for revocation of the detention pursuant to Subparagraph 4 of Paragraph 1 of Article 37 of the Act.
